        "eyebrow": "Our Vetting Process",
        "heading": "What Makes HARAMOON So Special?",
        "quote_text": "After spending decades subscribing to Western skincare brands and chasing claims without any improvement, I finally decided to give K-Beauty a try. At first I was hesitant, with the same frontliner ingredients like Hyaluronic Acid and Retinol, I couldn't imagine brands from Korea figured something out that Western formulas hadn't already. Little did I know how wrong I was, and to my surprise and delight, as my skin healed, improved, and yes, even glowed, I decided I was a proud convert. \n\n At the time K-Beauty was a brand new concept, and any Korean brands I was able to find at big box retailers were altered before hitting the shelves. Formulas tweaked, ingredients substituted here and there, and sometimes entire product lines were bought to then be sunsetted completely, I felt cheated for not having the kind of access most Americans expect. I decided I had to bring more of it to the states myself. After scouring dozens of brands and endless ingredient labels, I found HARAMOON.\n\nWhat initially attracted us to HARAMOON was their clean and minimalist formulas. Having oily, clog-prone skin, avoiding unnecessary ingredients was my main goal. \n\nSecond, Haramoon merges clinical results with natural care — skin-friendly and earth conscious. Formulated intentionally to strengthen the skin barrier, HARAMOON acts like a multivitamin, meeting the foundational needs for long term skin health and longevity. This attitude was something new to my Western eyes, something special.",
        "body_text": "I tested every product in the line on my own skin before I agreed to carry it, and today it's what I continue to use. The first thing I noticed? It was what I did not notice — no tightness after cleansing, no breakouts from switching, no fragrance headaches, no enlarged pores at the end of the day. That absence of reaction is the hardest thing to find in skincare, and it told me the formulas were doing exactly what they claimed. That is why Wax | Wane carries HARAMOON and is proud to be their first retail partner in the U.S.A.",
